          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                                        <date>9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of December 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>;</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir;</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">Encouraged by<lb/> the following sentence on the
                                                  356<hi rend="sup">th</hi> page of the<lb/>
                                        Occident of <date>October</date> last. “Of course we give only<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr. M's</persName> own statements, and should
                                        there be any<lb/> mistake, we will cheerfully insert a
                                        reply; our<lb/> only object being to do justice in the
                                        premises, and<lb/> to charge no one with wrong-doing,
                                        without the fullest<lb/> proof.” I therefore send you this
                                        article to be pub=<lb/>lished in the Occident in reply to
                                        one of <persName>Mr. Mar=<lb/>cussohn</persName> of
                                                  <date>October</date> last; and I feel confident,
                                        that<lb/> you will do us the favour and the justice,
                                                  <del>that you</del><lb/> to fulfill a promise made
                                        so public; all we ask<lb/> is justice &amp; no more. I do
                                        not wish, unless<lb/> compelled, to say or write any more
                                        about this<lb/> matter, but desire to live in harmony &amp;
                                        peace.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">However should you refuse to publish this<lb/>
                                        communication, though I have not the slightest<lb/> idea
                                        that you will, for you love justice as well as<lb/> myself,
                                        I shall be necessitated to vindicate the<lb/> conduct of the
                                        Jewish mission society, in reference<lb/> to this matter,
                                        not only in the Jewish Chronicle<lb/> but also in the public
                                        journals of this &amp; other cities<lb/> where Jews are,
                                        &amp; our mission society is represented.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Yours very sincerely</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">G. D. Bernheim</persName>
                              </p>
